@startuml
!include ../_style.puml

title UC-01: User Registration

actor User
participant "Entry-Hub" as EH <<service>>
participant "Security-Switch" as SS <<service>>
participant "Database-Vault" as DV <<service>>
participant "Storage-Service" as ST <<service>>
participant "Network-Manager" as NM <<service>>

note over User
  SSH keypair already generated client-side;
  the private key never leaves the client (CL-F-01)
end note

User -> EH : POST /api/register (HTTPS)\nemail, password, SSH public key
EH -> SS : forward request (mTLS)
SS -> DV : forward request (mTLS)

note over EH, DV
  Each hop independently re-validates the input.
  On failure: HTTP 400, request not forwarded further,
  issue logged without identifying the user (EH-F-06, SS-F-03, DV-F-02)
end note

DV -> DV : hash email (SHA-256) · encrypt email\nhash password (Argon2id)

alt email or SSH key already registered
  DV --> SS : 409 Conflict
  SS --> EH : 409 Conflict
  EH --> User : 409 Conflict
else no duplicate
  DV -> DV : save user record (atomic transaction)
  DV -> ST : create POSIX user "user<xxxxxx>" (mTLS)

  alt POSIX user creation fails
    ST --> DV : failure
    DV -> DV : delete user record (compensating rollback)
    DV --> SS : registration failed
    SS --> EH : 5xx
    EH --> User : 5xx
  else success
    ST --> DV : POSIX user created
    DV --> SS : registration success
    SS -> NM : create Headscale user + pre-auth key (mTLS)
    NM --> SS : pre-auth key
    SS --> EH : 201 Created + pre-auth key
    EH --> User : 201 Created + pre-auth key
  end
end

@enduml
